cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.AL, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with distributed algorithms for constructing spanners, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as likely categories. The use of communication complexity and information theory in proving lower bounds suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithmic complexity, which suggests cs.AL (Computational Complexity) as a possible category.
